{"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"anchor":"Overview","text":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Observation provides a robust, type-safe, and performant implementation of the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"observer design pattern in Swift. This pattern allows an observable object to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"maintain a list of observers and notify them of specific or general state"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"changes. This has the advantages of not directly coupling objects together and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"allowing implicit distribution of updates across potential multiple observers."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The Observation frameworks provides the following capabilities:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Marking a type as observable","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Tracking changes within an instance of an observable type","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Observing and utilizing those changes elsewhere, such as in an app’s user","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"interface","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To declare a type as observable, attach the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Observation\/Observable()"},{"type":"text","text":" macro"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to the type declaration. This macro declares and implements conformance to the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Observation\/Observable"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol to the type at compile time."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["@Observable","class Car {","    var name: String = \"\"","    var needsRepairs: Bool = false","    ","    init(name: String, needsRepairs: Bool = false) {","        self.name = name","        self.needsRepairs = needsRepairs","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To track changes, use the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Observation\/withObservationTracking(_:onChange:)"},{"type":"text","text":" function."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"For example, in the following code, the function calls the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"onChange"},{"type":"text","text":" closure"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"when a car’s name changes. However, it doesn’t call the closure when a car’s"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"needsRepair"},{"type":"text","text":" flag changes. That’s because the function only tracks properties"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"read in its "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"apply"},{"type":"text","text":" closure, and the closure doesn’t read the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"needsRepair"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"property."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["func render() {","    withObservationTracking {","        for car in cars {","            print(car.name)","        }","    } onChange: {","        print(\"Schedule renderer.\")","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"}],"kind":"content"}],"abstract":[{"text":"Make responsive apps that update the presentation when underlying data changes.","type":"text"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/swift\/observation-collection"]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/Observation-collection","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift"]]},"sections":[],"kind":"article","schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"metadata":{"role":"collectionGroup","title":"Observation","modules":[{"name":"Swift"}]},"references":{"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift":{"role":"collection","url":"\/documentation\/swift","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Build apps using a powerful open language."}],"title":"Swift","images":[{"identifier":"Swift-PageImage-card.png","type":"card"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift","kind":"symbol"},"Swift-PageImage-card.png":{"alt":"An orange Swift logo on a gradient background.","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/com.apple.Swift\/Swift-PageImage-card@2x.png","traits":["2x","light"]},{"url":"\/images\/com.apple.Swift\/Swift-PageImage-card~dark@2x.png","traits":["2x","dark"]}],"type":"image","identifier":"Swift-PageImage-card.png"}}}